FIRE SAFETY GUIDELINES AT THE AKIRACHIX CAMPUS
When a fire occurs everyone should move in a straight line walking towards the fire assembly point through the nearest fire exit.
Roll calls should be made to ensure everyone is present and safe.Everyone should check out for their classmates,colleagues and also roommates.Just in-case there is someone inside they need to use a wet blanket or a fire blanket to save the rest who are inside. 
First aid to be administered just in-case of any casualties present.Especially giving free airspace for the casualties if they inhaled too much smoke.
Using the correct fire extinguisher to put out the fire.Fire extinguishers are placed in several areas at the campus and their correct use for each specified area for example if it is a kitchen fire the correct extinguisher is a foam or water extinguisher.
All the AkiraChix community should undergo a thorough fire safety training in case of a fire and learn what is supposed to be done when a fire occurs.

